--- body ---
## Outcome (2026-07-10) — scope reduced, closed

The founding premise — "replicate the manuscript's clean-room freeze for the four
remaining papers" — is false. None of the four is an active in-repo submission:

- **Manuscript** is frozen in-repo *because* it is the live Œconomia R&R being
  rebuilt for resubmission (0153). That is the one legitimate in-repo freeze.
- **Data-paper** is already submitted (RDJ4HSS, sent 2026-03-26) and its frozen,
  reproducible form lives OUTSIDE the repo: `papiers/sent/RDJ4HSS_Curated_Corpus_
  Climate_Finance/` (PDF, Figure1, Table1-3, cover letter) plus a 208 MB Zenodo
  reproducibility archive `climate-finance-datapaper.tar.gz`. Per the 0159
  architecture rule (submission records live outside the repo), that IS the clean
  frozen state. Giving `content/data-paper.qmd` a second in-repo freeze would
  manufacture a drifting duplicate of an immutable deposit. Repo copy stays live.
- **corpus-report / technical-report / multilayer-detection** are not submitted —
  live companions whose numbers should track the corpus, not be pinned.

Freezing a live paper only manufactures staleness (which then needs a freshness
guard to patrol — the reason the 0212 follow-up was dropped). So the four keep
their existing data-dependent render rules in the main `Makefile` / `make papers`;
no per-paper `.mk`, no `.gitignore` negations, no vars pinning.

## Architecture rule (the reduced deliverable)

Documented in `README.md`:

> Clean-room build == the paper being (re)submitted from the repo. Only a paper
> pinned by an external commitment (submission / R&R) is frozen in-repo and built
> clean-room from git-tracked deliverables (Quarto + TeX Live + Pandoc — no `uv`,
> no `dvc`, no data). Today that is the manuscript (`manuscript.mk`). Every other
> document (corpus-report, technical-report, data-paper, multilayer-detection)
> builds LIVE from the corpus via `make papers`. An already-submitted paper's
> frozen form is its external deposit (`papiers/sent/…` + Zenodo), not an in-repo
> copy.

## What actually shipped under 0163 (this ticket's tracker)

- **0208** (merged, PR #969) — evicted the large analysis intermediates out of
  `content/tables/` into `data/derived/tables/`; `content/tables/` now holds only
  writing-facing deliverables. The real clean-build / de-crowding win.
- This ticket — the README architecture rule above.

## Exit criteria (revised)

- [x] Architecture rule documented in README (clean-room == active submission;
      live papers build from data; submitted papers frozen externally).
- [x] No spurious in-repo freezes introduced; the four remain live in `make papers`.
- [x] Superseded scope (per-paper `.mk` extraction + vars pinning) recorded as
      premise-falsified, not silently dropped.

